---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Privacy — Protein Check"
  description="How Protein Check handles your meal photos and data. Short version: your photo is analyzed in the moment and never stored."
  canonical="/privacy"
>
  <main id="main" class="legal">
    <p class="back"><a href="/">← Protein Check</a></p>
    <h1>Privacy</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated June 2026</p>

    <div class="tldr">
      <strong>The short version:</strong> No account, no tracking profile. Your meal photo is sent
      to Google's Gemini API to be analyzed and is <strong>not stored by us</strong>. We keep only the
      anonymous nutrition estimate (grams of protein and leucine, item names) to understand how the
      tool is used and to make it better.
    </div>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <p>When you analyze a meal, we receive the photo you choose, resized in your browser before it
      leaves your device. We send it to the Google Gemini vision API, which returns an estimate. We
      then store the <em>derived estimate</em> only: total protein, total leucine, the list of detected
      items, and a short verdict. We do not store the photo itself.</p>

    <h2>What we do not collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>We do not require an account, name, or email to use the tool.</li>
      <li>We do not store your meal photos.</li>
      <li>We do not sell data or share it with advertisers.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Third parties</h2>
    <p>Photos are processed by <a href="https://ai.google.dev/" rel="noopener">Google's Gemini API</a>
      under Google's terms. The site is hosted on Netlify and the API on Railway, which process
      standard request logs (such as IP address and timestamp) to operate the service.</p>

    <h2>Your data</h2>
    <p>Stored estimates are anonymous and not linked to your identity. If you have a question about
      data handling, email <a href="mailto:raj@withmagic.ai">raj@withmagic.ai</a>.</p>

    <h2>Accuracy</h2>
    <p>Estimates are AI-generated and approximate. Protein Check is for general information and is not
      medical or dietary advice. See the <a href="/terms">Terms</a>.</p>
  </main>

  <style>
    .legal { max-width:680px; margin:0 auto; padding:40px 20px 8px; }
    .back a { font-weight:600; font-size:14px; text-decoration:none; }
    .legal h1 { font-size:clamp(30px,7vw,42px); margin:18px 0 4px; }
    .updated { color:var(--ink-muted); font-size:13px; margin:0 0 24px; }
    .tldr { background:var(--accent-soft); color:var(--accent-ink); border-radius:var(--radius); padding:16px 18px; font-size:15px; line-height:1.6; margin-bottom:8px; }
    .legal h2 { font-size:20px; margin:30px 0 8px; }
    .legal p, .legal li { color:var(--ink-soft); font-size:15.5px; }
    .legal ul { padding-left:20px; }
    .legal li { margin:6px 0; }
  </style>
</Layout>
